The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, August 18, 2004 				 Mumbais millionaires lead the pack
																								New Delhi, Aug. 17 (PTI): Mumbai is home to Dharavi, Asias largest slum, but it also boasts of the largest number of millionaires in the country.																								As many as 18,939 Mumbai residents have declared an income of over Rs 10 lakh to the income tax department, the Rajya Sabha was informed today.																								Bangalore comes a distant second, with 13,130 millionaires, followed by Delhis 12,450 millionaires. 																								In all, the country has 70,217 millionaires, minister of state for finance S.S. Palanimanickam said in a written reply to a question in the Upper House.																								On the basis of returned income/loss, the number of individual assessees declaring income/loss of Rs 10 lakh or above as on September 30, 2003, were 70,127, he said.																								Among the other metros, Calcutta has 3,492 millionaires, Pune 4,198, Chennai 2,716, Hyderabad 3,835 and Ahmedabad 1,168.																								Even the smaller towns have quite a few millionaires to boast of: Allahabad has 76 millionaires, Amritsar 251, Baroda 665, Bareilly 46, Bhopal 146, Bhubaneswar 694, Chandigarh 489, Cochin 411, Coimbatore 512, Dehra Dun 199, Guwahati 165, Indore 298, Jaipur 531, Jodhpur 187, Kanpur 498, Lucknow 217, Ludhiana 515, Madurai 40, Meerut 254, Nagpur 397, Nashik 225, Panchkula 431, Patna 230, Raipur 64, Rajkot 110, Ranchi 138, Shillong 50, Shimla 80, Surat 587, Thane 821, Trichy 192, Thiruvananthapuram 429 and Udaipur 341.
